Phase 4 \emdash  Calendar View\par
The second primary view. A personal + community calendar.\par
\par
Steps:\par
\par
Install FullCalendar \emdash  @fullcalendar/core, @fullcalendar/react, @fullcalendar/daygrid, @fullcalendar/timegrid, @fullcalendar/interaction. Wrap in a client component with next/dynamic (ssr: false).\par
\par
CalendarView component \emdash  src/components/calendar/CalendarView.tsx. Full-height calendar that fills the content area. Month/week/day toggle buttons. Fetches events from Supabase on view.\par
\par
Event color coding \emdash  Three visual tiers:\par
\par
Your own events (created_by = user) \emdash  solid blue\par
RSVP'd events \emdash  solid green\par
Public community events \emdash  light purple/outlined\par
Category color as a subtle accent dot/stripe\par
Click date \f2\u8594?\f0  create event \f1\emdash  Clicking an empty date slot opens EventForm in the SlidePanel with the date pre-filled. User chooses visibility: public (appears on map for all) or private (personal calendar only).\par
\par
Click event \f2\u8594?\f0  detail panel \f1\emdash  Clicking a calendar event opens the SlidePanel with EventDetailContent. User can RSVP, view details, see location on mini-map.\par
\par
Public/private visibility \emdash  Update EventForm with a visibility toggle. Public events with coordinates appear as map markers. Private events only appear on the creator's calendar.\par
\par
Calendar \f3\u8596?\f0  Map interaction \f1\emdash  When viewing a public event's details from the calendar, a "Show on Map" button switches to map view and flies to that event's location.\par
\par
