Phase 5 \emdash  Reviews, Verification & Community\par
Social trust layer and ongoing place verification.\par
\par
Steps:\par
\par
Review/rating UI \emdash  src/components/reviews/ReviewCard.tsx, ReviewForm.tsx, ReviewList.tsx. Display on place and event detail panels. Star rating (1-5), optional comment, "Does this place still exist?" checkbox (for place reviews only). Aggregate rating displayed on markers and detail panels.\par
\par
Post-event attendance prompt \emdash  After an event's date passes, users who RSVP'd see an in-app notification/banner (not push notification yet) on their next visit: "How was [Event Name]? Rate 1-5". Store response in reviews. This could be a simple banner component at the top of the calendar view or a modal on app open.\par
\par
Place verification system \emdash  Two mechanisms:\par
\par
Community signals: If multiple users mark "this place no longer exists" in reviews, flag the place (auto-set is_verified = false after N negative signals). Show a warning badge on the marker.\par
Annual owner prompt: A Supabase Edge Function (cron) that runs monthly, finds places where verified_at is older than 11 months, and sends an email to the owner's profile email asking them to confirm. If no response within 30 days, place gets flagged. Owner can click a link to re-verify (sets verified_at = now()).\par
Aggregate ratings on markers \emdash  Show average rating as a small badge on map markers. Places with high ratings get a subtle glow or gold accent. Places flagged as possibly closed get a dimmed/strikethrough style.\par
\par
Invite/share \emdash  Generate shareable links for events and places. "Share" button in detail panel copies link or opens native share dialog (via navigator.share \emdash  works great in Capacitor).\par
\par
Relevant files:\par
