Phase 6 \emdash  Mobile (Capacitor)\par
Wrap the web app for app store distribution.\par
\par
Steps:\par
\par
Install Capacitor \emdash  @capacitor/core, @capacitor/cli, @capacitor/ios, @capacitor/android\par
Configure \emdash  npx cap init, point web directory to Next.js static export or use @capgo/capacitor-updater for live updates\par
Native plugins \emdash  @capacitor/geolocation (map centering), @capacitor/push-notifications (future), @capacitor/share (native share dialog), @capacitor/status-bar (style status bar)\par
Build & test \emdash  npx next build && npx next export && npx cap sync && npx cap open android/ios\par
This phase is mostly configuration, not app code changes, since the mobile-first UI is built in Phases 2-4.\par
\par
Decisions Captured\par
Places vs Events: fundamentally separate (places = permanent, events = time-bound)\par
Mobile: Capacitor wrapper, one codebase, mobile-first web UI\par
Calendar: FullCalendar library\par
Map: Raw Leaflet (no react-leaflet) \emdash  already proven pattern\par
Event marker encoding: temporal scale (live \f2\u8594?\f0  distant) controlling opacity, size, color\par
Place verification: dual approach (community "still exists?" signals + annual owner email)\par
Reviews: unified system for both places and events, 1-5 stars + comment\par
Roles: individual, ministry, organization, business (replacing vendor/client)\par
\par
